        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 4 at 3:54PM MDT until August 4 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>SVRMSO

The National Weather Service in Missoula has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
North central Deer Lodge County in west central Montana...
Southeastern Granite County in west central Montana...

* Until 430 PM MDT.

* At 353 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 12 miles south of
Philipsburg, or 17 miles west of Anaconda, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Georgetown and Porters Corner.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
